correctness.rationale: Largely incorrect and non-traceable. Key issues: (1) Multiple processes are described in the article (depositions at 170 °C and 400 °C; a special case at 200 °C without purge; and distinct O2 and N2 anneals), but only a single process is extracted. (2) Dosing/purge times are wrong by 1000×: the article reports 1 s (DEZ), 5 s (H2O), and 10 s purge; extraction uses units of milliseconds with numeric values 1, 5, 10 instead of 1000, 5000, 10000. (3) plasmaPower is set to null, which violates the schema (should be omitted or be a properly formed object; also not PEALD). (4) Many parameters are fabricated or unsupported: saturation=false, nucleationPeriod=5 cycles, growthPerCycle=0.1 Å/cycle, numberofCycles=2000, flow rates (10 sccm), deliveryMethod, reactor details—all not reported. The GPC, cycles, and thickness are internally inconsistent (0.1 Å × 2000 cycles = 20 nm vs filmThickness=200 nm). (5) Material/electrical/device properties are ungrounded: refractive index, absorption coefficient, band gap method (Tauc), XPS composition/ratio, XRD/polycrystalline, AFM roughness, film density, and all TFT device metrics are not in the article (which only reports PL features; e.g., FWHM 67.5 meV). (6) Safety, filmStability, reproducibility statements are not from the article. (7) Minor: carrierGas/purgingGas marked 'not specified' (acceptable as placeholders but not informative), and deliveryMethod could have been extracted as alternating dosing via separate inlet lines. Correct values traceable to the article include substrate (sapphire), precursor (DEZ), co-reactant (H2O), temperature range (170–400 °C; a single value of 170 °C is only one case), pressure (~0.3–0.5 Torr; 0.4 chosen), and film thickness (~200 nm). Most other entries should be removed or corrected to match the source and schema.

completeness.rationale: The extraction is largely incorrect and incomplete relative to the article and the schema. Key issues: (1) Missing processes: the article reports ALE/ALD ZnO depositions at two substrate temperatures (170 °C and 400 °C) and also a special deposition without purge at 200 °C; only one process (170 °C) is represented. Each deposition condition should be a separate process. (2) Fabricated and non-traceable values: growth-per-cycle (0.1 Å), number of cycles (2000), flow rates (10 sccm), nucleation period (5 cycles), saturation (False), uniformity (5%), conformality (AR=10), refractive index (2.0), absorption coefficient (0), density (5.6 g/dm3), film composition (50% with XPS), crystallinity (polycrystalline by XRD), and all device/TFT properties are not reported in the article. (3) Inconsistencies: GPC 0.1 Å with 2000 cycles contradicts the 200 nm thickness (should be ~1 Å/cycle to reach 200 nm). (4) Unit/time errors: dosing and purge times are given as 1, 5, and 10 with unit MilliSEC, but the article specifies 1 s, 5 s, and 10 s; the numeric values should be 1000, 5000, and 10000 ms if using MilliSEC. (5) Schema violations or questionable entries: plasmaPower is set to null (should be omitted or a valid object), and many required fields are populated with placeholders or invented values, harming traceability. (6) Missing reported details: the second deposition at 400 °C, the pressure range (0.3–0.5 Torr is given; a single value is acceptable but the second process should capture the temperature change), and reservoir temperature for precursors (10 °C) are not captured. Properties to add/review: add separate process for 400 °C (and, if considered, the no-purge 200 °C run), correct dosing/purge times and remove or justify all fabricated values (GPC, cycles, flows, uniformity, conformality, optical/electrical/device metrics). Ensure plasmaPower is omitted for thermal ALD and align film thickness controls with reported data.
